item.title: LBC America
item.description: The Lebanese Broadcasting Corporation’s trademark productions such as Kalam el Nas and Ahmar bil Khatt al Arid will bring Lebanon’s day-to-day life straight to your living room. LBC is the first private television station in Lebanon and currently one of the most popular. It is exclusively available in America on myTV.

item.title: Rotana Cinema
item.description: Rotana Cinema owns the largest and richest Arabic movie library in the world. Containing over 2000 premium production films, from golden oldies to the latest blockbusters never yet broadcasted on TV, and everything in between, it’s your ticket to the largest assortment of family entertainment, and the latest smash hits on the silver screen.

item.title: Rotana Music
item.description: The party never has to stop. Rotana Music broadcasts all the latest Arabic Music videos. Its most popular programs are Top 20, a show that launches all the new releases, and Rotana Café presenting the main developments on the music scene.

item.title: Rotana Clip
item.description: Watch great music videos around the clock on Rotana Clip.

item.title: Rotana Zaman
item.description: Although the evolution of filmmaking has rapidly taken over the entertainment industry, great classics still attract viewers of all ages. Preserving the Arab world’s film heritage is Rotana’s mission. They’ve assembled the biggest number of old movies in order to provide its audience with the rarest films in high resolution.

item.title: Rotana Khalijiya
item.description: Khalijiya is a lifestyle and fashion channel. Shows include: Kora show, Al Osboa Fi Faaha, Sayidaty, and Ya Hala.

item.title: Rotana Masriya
item.description: Egyptian general entertainment channel focusing on Egyptian shows, series and variety programs.

item.title: Rotana Classic
item.description: Your favorite Arabic Cinema classics.

item.title: Rotana Aflam
item.description: The ultimate destination for Arabic and international movies.

item.title: OTV
item.description: One of the youngest Lebanese television stations, OTV began broadcasting in July 2007 then was officially launched 6 months later, in 2008. OTV now covers the world through different broadcasting channels for Europe, North America, Australia, and the Middle East. Owned by OTV holding, the channels offers a rich and diversified grid with programs such as Kazadoo for kids, Oof Lebanese zajal show and Tech Today.

item.title: Future News
item.description: Launched in 2007, Future News is one of the latest ventures of the Future Television Network, a Lebanese owned company established in 1993. The 24-hours Lebanese news channel covers local, regional and international news from its headquarters in Beirut and with correspondents around the globe. Broadcasting mainly in Arabic, Future News’ comprehensive coverage includes politics, sports, entertainment, technology and many more with live news bulletins around the clock and large arrays of talk shows and award-winning documentaries.

item.title: AlJazeera News
item.description: With headquarters in Doha, Qatar; AlJazeera is an independent broadcaster, owned by the state of Qatar through the Qatar Media Corporation. Initially launched as an Arabic news and current affairs satellite TV channel, its coverage of dissenting views spurred controversy in the Arab states of the Persian Gulf. The network gained worldwide attention following the September 11, 2001 attacks, when it was the only channel to cover the war in Afghanistan live from its office there. It has also recently been acclaimed for its in-depth coverage of the Arab Spring protests and revolutions.

item.title: AlJazeera Sport
item.description: Launched in 2003, the popular Arabic-language sports channel broadcasts you favorite games live, as well as a variety of sports-related programs.

item.title: Alsumaria
item.description: Alsumaria is an independent Iraqi Satellite TV Network. Established by a group of professional businessmen in 2004, it embraces a moderate speech for a united Iraq, representative of all Iraqis. Through its programs and news bulletins, the network supports national approaches in building the Iraqi state on democratic values.

item.title: AlResalah
item.description: Launched in 2006, the Arabic-language religious channel broadcasts Islamic teachings and Muslim faith insights 24/7.

item.title: AlJadeed
item.description: Broadcasting from Lebanon and formerly known as New TV, AlJadeed offers general-interest programming in Arabic with groundbreaking shows such as Al Fasad and ChiNN. (Not available in the U.S and Canada)

item.title: Chabab TV
item.description: Established in 2011 and broadcasting from Iraq, Chabab Television offers a varied selection of music video clips to fit all tastes, including some exclusive new releases. This TV station enjoys a wide popularity, essentially amongst Iraqi youth in Iraq and all over the world.

item.title: NBN
item.description: National Broadcasting Network - NBN, is a Lebanese private company, founded in 1996. NBN is aiming to become the first news and thematic station in Lebanon.

item.title: Télé Lumière
item.description: Launched in 1991 in Lebanon, Télé Lumière is a non-profit organization with an ecumenical mission. It is supervised by the Assembly of Catholic Patriarchs and Bishops in Lebanon and directed by a committee of religious leaders from various denominations and a group of laity. Télé Lumière and its satellite station, Noursat, promote multi-cultural understanding and religious dialogue.,

item.title: Fatafeat
item.description: A unique concept in the Middle East, Dubai-based Fatafeat is a channel devoted to food and the culinary arts. It’s a delicious gastronomic journey through the delights of exotic flavors as well as wholesome traditional recipes with cooking shows in Arabic and English such a Houriyat Al Matbakh, Nigella Lawson’s Nigella Kitchen and Italia Maa Lydia.

item.title: Al Yawm
item.description: A lifestyle and general variety television channel with a distinct regional flavor. Premium entertainment programming includes talk shows, cooking shows, television series, and also programs aimed at women with a focus on style and beauty, health, nutrition and medical. “Arabic entertainment at its best”

item.title: Cinema 1
item.description: 24/7 regional contemporary Arabic movie channel showcasing daily and weekly thematic appointments and a premium collection of drama, action, music, thrillers, romance and comedy. “The Golden Screen of Arabic Cinema”.

item.title: Cinema 2
item.description: 24/7 Classic Arabic family movie channel specializing in Egyptian movies and classics. Monthly tributes and thematic appointments. “Your window to cinema classics”.

item.title: Fann
item.description: Covers all forms of musical arts and culture: modern or classical Arabic and Gulf concerts, Khaliji, Tarab, and much more! “The Arts Channel”.

item.title: Mousalsalat
item.description: Features a premium collection of Arabic television drama series from the Middle East, it undisputedly presents the most famous television productions from regional drama. Its own exclusive productions, “The Jewel of Arabic Drama”.

item.title: Music now
item.description: Plays rhythms and melodies from around the world with a unique blend of global flavors specifically targeted at the Middle Eastern and North African markets. 24/7 music international and regional clips. All day greatest hits with prime time programming appointments.

item.title: AlSafwa
item.description: Broadcasts an original collection of regional programming, which includes political and social talk shows, documentaries, historical and religious drama series, “The Elite Arabic Channel”.

item.title: Télé Liban
item.description: Télé Liban (TL) became the first Lebanese public television network, owned by the Lebanese government. Currently, it mainly broadcasts terrestrially throughout Lebanon. TL is the Lebanese member of the European Broadcasting Union (EBU).

item.title: Mousalsalat +4
item.description: If you are finding it hard to keep an appointment with the best series on Mousalsalat, the Series Channel; simply switch to Mousalsalat +4, a time shift channel that broadcasts the same series on the Series Channel four hours later.

item.title: Roya TV
item.description: A Jordanian channel that addresses youth as well as the whole family. It is the first destination for information and entertainment for Jordanians around the world.

item.title: Arab Woman TV
item.description: The First Channel dedicated to the Arab Women; it tackles multiple issues concerning women and families rights, educational and health problems, and it focuses also on fashion, beauty and cooking, as well as a variety of other subjects related to the Arab world women."

item.title: Iqraa
item.description: Founded in 1998, Iqraa addresses Muslim families and offers religious and social programming from an Islamic perspective, with a modern vision. (Not available in the U.S)

item.title: Iqraa international
item.description: An edutainment channel in English for non-Arab Muslims. It focuses on the teachings of Islam and addresses various segments of the family.

item.title: Taha TV
item.description: A Lebanon-based Islamic channel for children aged 2-12 years old.

item.title: Karameesh
item.description: A Jordanian entertainment channel broadcasting songs, fun shows and light programs for children.

item.title: Karameesh plus
item.description: A Jordanian education and entertainment channel broadcasting children’s programs in Arabic with a focus on Islamic teachings.

item.title: Sana TV
item.description: A kids channel aimed at educating children while providing entertainment.

item.title: Assoufia TV
item.description: An international Islamic channel dedicated to programs praising Islam and the Prophet.

item.title: AlJazeera English
item.description: Broadcasts news features and analysis, documentaries, live debates, current affairs, business, technology, and sports. AlJazeera English is the world's first English-language news channel headquartered in the Middle East.

item.title: AlJazeera Egypt Mubasher
item.description: Live from Egypt: news features and analysis, documentaries, debates, current affairs, business, technology, and sports. Al Jazeera is the world's first news channel headquartered in the Middle East.
